-- DPJ Lawmakers Praise Bank of Japan Action, Saying Move Is `Small Scale'
-- B y   T a k a s h i   H i r o k a w a
-- 2010-10-14T23:12:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/dpj-lawmakers-praise-bank-of-japan-action-saying-action-is-small-scale-.html
A group of ruling Democratic Party
of Japan legislators praised recent steps by the Bank of Japan
to fight deflation, while calling the action “small scale.”  The group, who call themselves the “anti-deflation
lawmakers,” issued a statement today reiterating calls for
changes to the Bank of Japan law and the selection process for
its governor and board members.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Takashi Hirokawa in Tokyo at 
 thirokawa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Austin at 
 billaustin@bloomberg.net  